2, Electrooculogram (EG) to measure eye movements using electrodes placed near the outer
canthus of each eye.

3. Asubmenial electromyogram (EMG) to measure submental electromyographie activity using
electrodes placed over the mentalis, submentals muscle, and/or masseter regions.

4, Rhythm electrocardiogram (ECG). Modified V2 placement.

55, Nasal andior oral airflow via both thermistor and nasal pressure sensor.

plethysmography, endoesophageal pressure andlor by intercostal EMG.

8. Bilateral anterior tibialis muscle activity, motor activity-movement using EMG.

9. Body positions by directly applied sensors or by direct observation.
